  "reasoning": "The bug is a race condition in the RPC signal handling code. In __rpc_execute (line 783-792), when a sync RPC task receives a signal while waiting (out_of_line_wait_on_bit returns -ERESTARTSYS), the code unconditionally calls rpc_exit(task, -ERESTARTSYS) which overwrites task->tk_status with error -512, even if the NFS server has already responded and the response is queued for processing. This causes NFS inode revalidation to fail with error -512, leading to autofs mount unmount. The fix is to check if the RPC response has already been received (task->tk_rqstp->rq_reply_bytes_recvd > 0) before unconditionally marking the task as failed with ERESTARTSYS. If the response was received, the task should be allowed to continue processing the response normally instead of being forced into an error state."
}

